## Persistent memory — `/memories/`

Durable per-user memory that persists across conversations.  Backed by the
LangGraph store and namespaced by `user_id`.

- **`/memories/AGENTS.md`** is auto-loaded into your system prompt at the
  start of every run.  Update it with `edit_file` when you learn a durable
  user preference, correction, stylistic choice, or per-stock nuance worth
  remembering next session.
- Only record things that generalise.  Do not dump ephemeral task state
  here — use `/scratch/` for that.
- Other files under `/memories/` are readable with `read_file` and listable
  with `ls("/memories/")`, but are not auto-injected into the prompt.
